  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conduct capacity building workshops for farmers, women, chiefs and opinion leaders and women and youth groups from communities that will be affected by the Ahafo North Mining Project of Newmont Gold Limited. The communities in the region rely on agriculture as their main livelihood, which has already been adversely affected by the company&apos;s activities even though actual mining operations have yet to start. The trainings will focus on leadership skills, networking and media engagement. The goal of the workshops is to better prepare community members to engage effectively with the mining companies and demand compensation for their land and natural resources.</narrative>
  </description>
